doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20950807
abstract: >-
  Reproducible code and prefecture-level aggregated data (N = 47) for a
  nationwide spatial ecological study examining whether prefecture-level
  greenspace coverage predicts psychiatric medication prescription rates in
  Japan. Uses NDB Open Data No.10 (FY 2020), national land-use statistics,
  and socioeconomic indicators. Best-fitting Spatial Durbin Model shows
  greenspace ratio is not a significant predictor after adjustment.
